{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb41a834-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s421"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"421"},"text":"§ 421.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Examination of plates and dies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of the Treasury may examine the plates, dies, bed pieces, and other material used in the printing of Federal Reserve notes and issue regulations relating to such examinations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb41a835-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6/s16"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6, § 16","children":[],"tail":" (par.), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/267"},"text":"38 Stat. 267","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/325/tVI/s602/g/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–325, title VI, § 602(g)(6)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-23"},"text":"Sept. 23, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2293"},"text":"108 Stat. 2293","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb41a836-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb41a837-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddb41a838-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of the tenth (formerly the eleventh) par. of section 16 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1913-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913","children":[],"tail":". For classification to this title of other pars. of section 16, see Codification note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s411"},"text":"section 411 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddb41a839-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/325"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–325","children":[],"tail":", which directed general amendment of “[t]he 11th undesignated paragraph of section 16 of the Federal Reserve Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s421"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 421","children":[],"tail":")”, was executed to this section to reflect the probable intent of Congress. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The examination of plates, dies, bed pieces, and so forth, and regulations relating to such examination of plates, dies, and so forth, of national-bank notes provided for in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s108"},"text":"section 108 of this title","children":[],"tail":", is extended to include notes herein provided for.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
